You're comparing apples and oranges.  <br>
<br>
a) Adding a rule that you have to have the pearl to be on the list doesn't physically change the list (in terms of # of people) .<br>
<br>
b) Adding a rule that says you cannot switch spots with someone does not physically change the list.<br>
<br>
c) By the definition of the new rule, it MUST be retroactive.  You say you have no problem with the first rule, as it is the right thing to be done.  Then why not the second rule?  Yes, you have a vested interest in the rule.  Well, so do I.  As does every other person on the list.  I do not know you, or many of the other clerics.  What I DO know is that clerics have been offered money for their spots.  Which is obviously unfair.  I'm not saying you are doing this, but that not having the rule leaves it open for such things.  Let's try and see how a new rule HELPS us, and not how it is deliberately made to screw us over.  This works for alot of things in life, so if you dont look at things this way, ya might wanna try =)<br>
